  p I'm also like 6 months into my investment training at <a href="https://www.pjmueller.de/">Geldhochschule</a>. Still in paper trading (simulation).

  h2#media Media
  h3 Ongoing Comics and Manga
  p Where I'm on the latest chapter or issue. That is: I'm reading them as they come out.
  p Ordered by my current enjoyment:

  ul
    li <a href="https://manga4life.com/manga/The-Fable">The Fable</a>
      ul
        li <b>What this is</b>: The worlds best hitman is told to take a break and spend a year among regular people.
        li <b>Why is it worth reading</b>: The story paints real characters that find themselves in unfamiliar circumstances. The manga does not shy away from adult themes (unlike Shonen Jumps Sakamoto Days) and just keeps you engaged.
    li <a href="https:///manga4life.com/manga/Onepunch-Man">Onepunch-Man</a>
      ul
        li <b>What this is</b>: Superheroes but the main character can beat everything in one punch.
        li <b>Why is it worth reading</b>: Funny, good fights and a huge cast of side characters with a lot of different perspectives that clash in large-scale battles.
    li <a href="https://www.webtoons.com/en/super-hero/unordinary/rss?title_no=679">Unordinary</a>
      ul
        li <b>What this is</b>: Superheroes in high school, dominated by a power level hierarchy.
        li <b>Why is it worth reading</b>: Propably the least thought-out thing on here. Plot holes everywhere and the art is lack-luster. An enjoyable read nonetheless.
    li <a href="https://getcomics.info/other-comics/the-walking-dead-deluxe-1-2020/">The Walking Dead Deluxe</a>
      ul
        li <b>What this is</b>: Zombie outbreak: A world suddenly without a government and modern technology. A story on people dealing with this.
        li <b>Why is it worth reading</b>: It's THE zombie comic for a reason. Detailed world that has the time to really be built up and explored over 200 issues. The deluxe version is a republishing, so you can follow allow as they come out without the huge back catalog looming over you.
    li <a href="https:///manga4life.com/manga/Jagaaaaaan">Jagaaaaaan</a>
      ul
        li <b>What this is</b>: Some peoples desires are realized through powers, but they can overtake you until you are a mindless monster.
        li <b>Why is it worth reading</b>: I thought I knew where this story was heading, but then it pulled the rug out under me. And repeatedly so.
    li <a href="https:///manga4life.com/manga/My-Home-Hero">My Home Hero</a>
      ul
        li <b>What this is</b>: You're a normal guy that has just murdered somebody to save their daugther. What do you do now?
        li <b>Why is it worth reading</b>: Realistic world wherein the details matter. It feels like a real scenario instead of a concocted story. The first part is well worth a read as our dad ingenuitively finds himself in various sticky situations. The second part still has to pan out for me.
    li <a href="https://getcomics.info/other-comics/oblivion-song-by-kirkman-and-de-felici-1-2018/">Oblivion Song</a>
      ul
        li <b>What this is</b>: Humanity found an Alien dimension. And the political and personal stories that evolve as humanity ties to cope the with resulting problems.
        li <b>Why is it worth reading</b>: Keeps you on your toes, as Kirkman keeps pushing the story with new revelations and twists.
    li <a href="https://getcomics.info/other-comics/stillwater-1-2020/">Stillwater</a>
      ul
        li <b>What this is</b>: Going in blind is best. Not a scenario I've seen before though. The political and personal ramifications of the scenario are explored.
        li <b>Why is it worth reading</b>: Getting thrown into the scenario along the with main character is exciting. Jury is still out on the current arc (by far the shorted comic on here).
    // li <a href="https:///manga4life.com/manga/Kaguya-Wants-To-Be-Confessed-To">Kaguya-Wants-To-Be-Confessed-To</a>
